# Example environment configuration for AFRI
# 
# For production (Netlify): Set GENAI_API_KEY via Netlify dashboard only
# For development: Create .env.local (git-ignored) with your development key
#
# IMPORTANT SECURITY NOTES:
# - NEVER commit .env.local to git
# - NEVER expose API keys in client-side code (VITE_* variables)
# - Rotate keys immediately if accidentally exposed
# - Use server-side environment variables only for production

# Server-side Gemini API key (set in Netlify environment variables for production)
# GENAI_API_KEY=your_key_here

# Optional: Gemini model selection (defaults to gemini-2.5-flash)
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash

# Development only: Client-side key for rapid prototyping (INSECURE - DO NOT USE IN PRODUCTION)
# Uncomment only for local development, and NEVER commit to git
# VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=your_dev_key_here
